This article relies largely or entirely on a [single source](/Wikipedia:Articles_with_a_single_source), which is less than ideal. One would think, given the gravity of the subject, that more rigorous documentation would have been readily available. Nevertheless, we endeavor to illuminate the events, though the paucity of sources leaves certain shadows where clarity should reside. Relevant discussion may be found on the [talk page](/Talk:Georgia_in_the_American_Revolution). Perhaps someone with a more *complete* understanding might contribute. Please help improve this article by [introducing citations to additional sources](/Help:Referencing_for_beginners). Find sources: "Georgia in the American Revolution" – news, newspapers, books, scholar, JSTOR (May 2018).

